            <div class="article" style="text-align:justify">
                Older adults become physically and mentally weakened as they age, their ability to respond to bullying and aggression also becomes weaker. The forms of elder abuse include not only physical but also mental torture and neglect.<br>
                In this section we will list 6 common types of elder abuse.
            </div>
